---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout 
  title="Fusion 360 Model Export Guide" 
  description="Learn how to export Fusion 360 models"
>
  <main class="min-h-screen bg-base-50 dark:bg-base-900">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-16">
      <h1 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold text-base-900 dark:text-white mb-8">
        Using Fusion 360 Models with the Portfolio Site
      </h1>
      
      <div class="prose dark:prose-invert max-w-none">
        <p>This guide explains how to export Fusion 360 models for use with the model-viewer component.</p>
        
        <h2>Supported Formats</h2>
        <p>The model-viewer component supports 3D models in the following formats:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>glTF/GLB</strong> (preferred format)</li>
          <li><strong>USDZ</strong> (for iOS AR experiences)</li>
        </ul>
        
        <h2>Exporting from Fusion 360</h2>
        
        <h3>Direct Export to glTF/GLB</h3>
        <ol>
          <li>In Fusion 360, go to File &gt; Export</li>
          <li>Select glTF format</li>
          <li>Choose GLB option</li>
          <li>Configure export settings</li>
          <li>Click Export and save the file</li>
        </ol>
        
        <h3>Using an Intermediate Format</h3>
        <p>If direct export isn't available:</p>
        <ol>
          <li>Export as OBJ format</li>
          <li>Convert OBJ to glTF/GLB using online tools</li>
        </ol>
        
        <h2>Adding Models to the Portfolio</h2>
        <ol>
          <li>Host your GLB file</li>
          <li>Create a JSON file in the models content directory</li>
          <li>Follow the example template structure</li>
        </ol>
        
        <h2>Optimizing Models</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>Simplify complex geometries</li>
          <li>Keep file sizes under 10MB</li>
          <li>Use compressed textures</li>
        </ul>
        
        <div class="mt-12 border-t border-base-200 dark:border-base-700 pt-8">
          <a href="/BonominiBlog/models/" class="text-accent-600 dark:text-accent-400 hover:underline">
            Back to Models
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </main>
</Layout>
